06/10/2009
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- An Ohrid court ordered on Monday (October 5th) a 30-day extension of the custody of the captain of the Ilinden ship, which sank in Lake Ohrid on September 5th, killing fifteen Bulgarian tourists onboard. 
The 23-year-old captain of the boat, Sotir Fileski, was arrested shortly after the incident. 
Experts are expected to publish their final conclusions about the reasons for the tragedy soon. 
(A1, Sitel, Alsat, MIA - 05/10/09)
